<task id="063" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4">
  <metadata>
    <title>B-7: Extract useEventsBulkActions hook into @spaarke/events-components</title>
    <phase>Phase 6 — Build hygiene cluster</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>3</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>none</dependencies>
    <blocks>064, 067</blocks>
    <tags>frontend, react, refactoring, hooks</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Code implementation refactor on .ts/.tsx files; modifies shared library + two consumers; tagged `react` (UI behavior parity required). FULL per Step 3.5.5 (modifies code with cross-package reuse + ADR-012 constraint + behavior-parity requirement).</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>H</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Per spec FR-10 / plan B-7: extract the `useEventsBulkActions` hook (currently expressed
    as inline `executeBulkStatusUpdate` / `executeBulkArchive` functions in
    `src/solutions/EventsPage/src/App.tsx`) into a new shared hook at
    `src/client/shared/Spaarke.Events.Components/src/hooks/useEventsBulkActions.ts`. Both
    `EventsPage` and the embedded Calendar widget (via `CalendarWorkspaceWidget`) MUST
    consume the same hook — single source of truth. Behavior MUST be identical in both
    surfaces. Per ADR-012, the hook is context-agnostic: dependencies (auth, webApi shim,
    notification dispatch) are injected, not imported from host code.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE React/TypeScript developer with shared-component (ADR-012) and hooks-extraction
    experience. Bias toward minimum-surface API: the hook takes deps as arguments, returns
    a small typed action API. No host-knowledge inside the hook. The Calendar widget's
    R3 task 115 "Pattern D" (shared-lib widget + thin LegalWorkspace shim) is the canonical
    reference for the consumption pattern.
  </role>

  <goal>
    (1) New hook file `src/client/shared/Spaarke.Events.Components/src/hooks/useEventsBulkActions.ts`
    exporting a typed `useEventsBulkActions(deps)` hook with `updateStatus`, `closeEvents`,
    `cancelEvents`, `holdEvents`, `archiveEvents` actions (or equivalent — match the actual
    EventsPage surface). (2) `Spaarke.Events.Components/src/hooks/index.ts` re-exports it.
    (3) `Spaarke.Events.Components/src/index.ts` re-exports from the hooks barrel. (4)
    `EventsPage/src/App.tsx` consumes the hook — old inline `executeBulkStatusUpdate` /
    `executeBulkArchive` removed. (5) Calendar widget consumer (likely
    `CalendarWorkspaceWidget.tsx` or its parent) wired to use the hook for parity. (6)
    Behavior MUST be identical to today in both surfaces — manual smoke test plus the
    UI tests below pass. FR-10 acceptance satisfied.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per backlog B-7 + plan §6 B-7: bulk-action logic for events (status update, archive,
      close, cancel, hold) is currently inline in `src/solutions/EventsPage/src/App.tsx`
      (~lines 718-1000). The Calendar widget (Pattern D dual-use, shipped R3 task 115)
      either duplicates this or doesn't yet expose bulk actions — confirm during step 1.
      Extracting to a shared hook removes the duplication risk and establishes the canonical
      pattern for Calendar to opt into bulk operations. Task 064 (B-8) follows immediately
      and works in the same package; this task's hook is the foundation it depends on.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/solutions/EventsPage/src/App.tsx</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.Events.Components/src/hooks/index.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.Events.Components/src/hooks/useEventsBulkActions.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.Events.Components/src/index.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.Events.Components/src/widgets/CalendarWorkspaceWidget/CalendarWorkspaceWidget.tsx</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">Shared hook MUST be context-agnostic. Dependencies (auth, webApi, notification dispatch, eventId-list source) are passed via the hook's argument; NO host-specific imports inside the hook.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Any UI surfaces touched MUST use Fluent UI v9 tokens only — no hex/rgba/v8. The hook itself is non-UI, but consumer wiring MUST preserve v9 token usage.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-022">React 19 only for Code Pages; the hook MUST be compatible (no React 16/17/18-only patterns like deprecated `useEffect` cleanup variants).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">If the hook needs a BFF call (it shouldn't — bulk actions are Dataverse Xrm.WebApi today), it MUST take `authenticatedFetch` as an injected dep, NOT import from `@spaarke/auth` directly. NO token snapshots.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Behavior MUST be identical to today's `EventsPage` inline implementation. NO bug fixes / refactors smuggled in — pure code-move. Defects discovered are captured as carry-over notes, not addressed here.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Hook MUST be typed (no `any` for the deps argument or the action return). Use the existing `EventStatus` enum + the `IEventRecord` (or equivalent) types from `@spaarke/events-components/src/types/`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">EventsPage redeploy is NOT part of this task — that lives in task 066 (B-10). This task only does the lib + consumer rewire.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-012-shared-components.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-design-system.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-022-react-19-code-pages.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-028-spaarke-auth-architecture.md</file>
