      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/plan.original.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/CLAUDE.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Pattern D dual-use widget" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.Events.Components/src/widgets/CalendarWorkspaceWidget/CalendarWorkspaceWidget.tsx">Reference for thin-shim consumption pattern (R3 task 115). The Calendar widget composes shared components; the bulk-actions hook follows the same shared/context-agnostic placement.</pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Inventory inline bulk-action logic">Read `EventsPage/src/App.tsx` lines ~700-1000 (functions: `executeBulkStatusUpdate`, `executeBulkArchive`, the EventStatus enum usage, the toast/notification calls). Catalog: function signatures, deps actually used (Xrm.WebApi or BFF? notification dispatch?), error-handling shape. Confirm Calendar widget consumer does or doesn't currently expose bulk actions.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Design hook API">Sketch `useEventsBulkActions(deps)` signature: deps shape (e.g., `{ webApi, notify, refreshEvents }`), return shape (e.g., `{ closeEvents, cancelEvents, holdEvents, archiveEvents, updateStatus, isProcessing }`). Verify the API supports both EventsPage and Calendar widget needs. Write to `notes/b7-hook-api-sketch.md` for review.</step>
    <step order="3" name="Implement hook">Create `src/client/shared/Spaarke.Events.Components/src/hooks/useEventsBulkActions.ts`. Copy logic verbatim from inline functions; replace direct globals with the injected deps. Export the hook + a `useEventsBulkActionsDeps` type. NO host-specific code.</step>
    <step order="4" name="Wire barrel exports">Add to `Spaarke.Events.Components/src/hooks/index.ts`: `export * from "./useEventsBulkActions";`. Add to `Spaarke.Events.Components/src/index.ts`: `export * from "./hooks";` (if not already exporting hooks barrel). Verify with a small grep.</step>
    <step order="5" name="Rewire EventsPage consumer">Edit `EventsPage/src/App.tsx`: import `useEventsBulkActions` from `@spaarke/events-components` (or relative path if alias not set). Call the hook at the top of the component with the right deps (xrm shim, notification handler, refresh callback). Replace each call site of `executeBulkStatusUpdate` / `executeBulkArchive` with the hook's exported actions. Delete the old inline implementations.</step>
    <step order="6" name="Wire Calendar widget consumer">If Calendar widget currently exposes bulk actions (verify in step 1), wire it the same way. If not, ensure the hook is *callable* from CalendarWorkspaceWidget — at minimum, prove parity by writing a small smoke component or test (do NOT add a UI surface that doesn't exist in Calendar today; this task is hook extraction, not Calendar feature addition).</step>
    <step order="7" name="Build verification">Run `npm run build` on `src/client/shared/Spaarke.Events.Components/`. Run `npm run build` on `src/solutions/EventsPage/`. 0 errors. Type-check `tsc --noEmit` on both — clean.</step>
    <step order="8" name="Lint clean">Run `npm run lint` on both packages (if scripts exist). 0 errors. If lint surfaces previously-hidden warnings, do NOT bundle the fixes here — record carry-overs to task 067 (B-11 type-drift).</step>
    <step order="9" name="UI smoke + parity test">Run the &lt;ui-tests&gt; below. Confirm bulk actions behave identically in EventsPage. (Calendar parity test deferred to manual operator check unless Calendar already exposed bulk actions.)</step>
    <step order="10" name="Update TASK-INDEX">Edit `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: flip task 063 from 🔲 → ✅ completed.</step>
    <step order="11" name="Document deviations">If hook API needed adjustment from sketch, or if Calendar consumer wiring was deferred (no current Calendar bulk-action surface), record in `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/notes/` for R4 lessons-learned.</step>
  </steps>

